posts.description: Once in a while I can actually contribute to #asundaycarpic and try to pretend I don't have numerous pictures of wisteria I haven't yet sharedüòÖ

With my camera roll still full of pictures from Spain I'd love to share a few shots of London in between. 
It's just a week left till @creatingforgood creative conference and we are all actively preparing to make this day memorable for all of you. Tap the photo to see all the wonderful ladies that will be doing workshops on the day - you can learn food photography and styling, camera settings, mobile photography photo editing and composition, how to use Instagram stories and so much more! The day will finish with cocktails and you also can get an individual consultation from any of @creatingforgood members! The full programme is now available at @creatingforgood, and what's more all the proceeds will go to support @womenforwomenuk!

There's something special about the light in Barcelona. As much as I prefer photographing London on a cloudy day, shooting in Barcelona on a sunny day is a completely different experience. The buildings are much taller and the way the light falls is just amazing!‚ú®

Another amazing building in Barcelona, Casa Amatller @casamuseuamatller. Together with the adjacent Casa Batll√≥ (on my first picture from Barcelona) and the Casa Lle√≥ Morera, it is part of the "mansana de la disc√≤rdia" or so called block of discord of Barcelona, because it features buildings in sharply contrasting styles. Actually I really like this corner as it looks so distinctiveüòä

During our short stay in Barcelona we saw so many beautiful places that I could be sharing pictures for the next 2 weeks! This is one of the beautiful details of @elnacionalbcn, an incredibly beautiful space of 4 different restaurants and 4 bars - all under one roof.

Palau de la Musica Catalana, a place I wanted to visit for a long time, is an amazing example of Catalan Art Nouveau architecture. Many thanks to @palaumusicacat and @casabatllo for giving us a private tour of the building and the opportunity to see the concert rehearsal and then the consent itself in the main hall. If you are in Barcelona, I'd highly recommend to visit either on a guided tour or for a concert.

Hola Barcelona! I'm very excited to be here with @casabatllo for the celebration of Sant Jordi. Casa Battlo is an amazing masterpiece by Antoni Gaudi, whose creations are always inspired by nature. For this weekend only Casa Battlo is decorated with roses that is part of Sant Jordi tradition - men give roses to women and women give books to men. #casabattlo #mesqueunarosa
When all London is covered with wisteria, shops included!üçÉ

Still thinking about yesterday's flower workshop with @londonflowerschool and @wagnerjk - I learned how to make natural flower arrangements which appeared to be very therapeutic! I got to take those gorgeous flowers home with me and surprisingly they've survived the tube ride very well! 
In other news @creatingforgood creative conference programme is now published on the website and there will be so many interesting workshops! All the profits will go to support @womenforwomenuk. Please let me know if any of you is planning to come - would be great to see you there!
Another place, not everyone knows about - library at @vamuseum. It's a very beautiful space and anyone can apply for a reader's ticket free of charge! Love V&A!
Those splashes of colour everywhere! They are easy to spot from the distance too and as much as you try to avoid taking another picture you can't help itüòÖ

You will be surprised to hear that those peaceful hills with sheep are in the middle of Auckland. It's been almost a week since I'm back and I have just shared my favourite viewpoints and coffee shops of Auckland on my blog (link in bio). Another post about other amazing spots on the North Island coming soon so stay tuned!
